Venezuela new 500-bolívar note (B391a) reportedly introduced 16.08.2024

2024-08-18

B391 (PNL): 500 bolívaresOrange, brown, and green. Front (vertical): Spanish text; radiant suns; BCV on Venezuelan map as registration device; three portraits of Simón Bolívar. Back: Spanish text; Venezuelan coat of arms; Puente Rafael Urdaneta (General Rafael Urdaneta cable-stayed bridge at Tablazo Strait outlet of Lake Maracaibo); Batalla Naval enRead More…

Armenia new sig/date (2024) 10,000-dram note (B322b) reported introduced 15.08.2024

2024-08-16

Like B322a, but new signatures (Galstyan/Hovhannisyan), new date (2024), 10000 on back in purple-to-green OVI, and UV improvements front/back. Courtesy of Alex Zlotin and Nune Teryan (Central Bank of Armenia).Read More…
